data.title: Dale Brown, former college basketball coach, is greeted
data.meta_description: Download Image of Dale Brown, former college basketball coach, is greeted. Free for commercial use, no attribution required. Dale Brown, former college basketball coach, is greeted by Airmen from the 91st Missile Wing at Minot Air Force Base, N.D., Sept. 8, 2015. As a part of their base visit, Brown, Shaquille O’Neal, former professional basketball player, and Kevin Cramer, congressman, toured a B-52H Stratofortress, the Uniform 1 missile training facility, McAdoo Fitness Center, the base theater and Rockers Bar and Grill to meet with and speak to Minot personnel and families. (U.S. Air Force photo/ Airman 1st Class Justin T. Armstrong). Dated: 08.09.2015. The objects in this collection are from The U.S. National Archives and Defense Visual Information Distribution Service. The U.S. National Archives and Records Administration (NARA) was established in 1934 by President Franklin Roosevelt. NARA keeps those Federal records that are judged to have continuing value—about 2 to 5 percent of those generated in any given year. There are approximately 10 billion pages of textual records; 12 million maps, charts, and architectural and engineering drawings; 25 million still photographs and graphics; 24 million aerial photographs; 300,000 reels of motion picture film; 400,000 video and sound recordings; and 133 terabytes of electronic data. The Defense Visual Information Distribution Service provides a connection between world media and the American military personnel serving at home and abroad. All of these materials are preserved because they are important to the workings of Government, have long-term research worth, or provide information of value to citizens.
